==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nisus
<hw>Ni"sus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>niti</ets>, p. p. <ets>nisus</ets>, to strive.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A striving; an effort; a conatus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>nisus</qex> or energizing towards a presented object.</q>
<rj><qau>Hickok.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The periodic
procreative desire manifested in the spring by birds, etc.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The contraction of the diaphragm and abdominal muscles
to evacuate feces or urine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nit</ent>⟦br⟧
